RealBiz Media Group, Inc. Releases Product Upgrades for Its NestBuilder Portal



Share Article

















Company outlines new development that is expected for launch in early April






Fort Lauderdale, Florida (PRWEB)
March 12, 2015
 RealBiz Media Group, Inc. (OTCQB: RBIZ), announces its new upgrades for NestBuilder with an expected launch the first week of April.
NestBuilder is both a consumer and agent driven portal, which proudly boasts the largest collection of listing videos on the web. Until recently, NestBuilder has focused on consumer acquisition and experience on the front-facing side of the website. In early April, however, NestBuilder will be releasing its latest, and biggest, upgrade to date. The update will include a comprehensive backend office for real estate professionals. The backend will include productivity tools which will allow agents to manage/promote listings, manage and schedule social media posts and keep track of their client list with a full-fledged CRM system. The software will be released as, “NestBuilder PowerAgent.” The program is set to have affordable options, starting at $9 monthly and more comprehensive packages around the $149 monthly price-point. This backend system, combined with the consumer-facing website, will establish NestBuilder as a ‘go to’ product for any real estate agent.
NestBuilder’s PowerAgent will allow full integrations with client lists and give agents the ability to send out messages to their entire address book with just a couple of clicks. PowerAgent will also allow them to track actions as well as set reminders and to-dos for follow ups with clients. “We have this amazing portal with a wonderful look and feel, and now we’re taking the good looks and giving it the brains to back it up with this new productivity tool,” said Alex Aliksanyan, CIO of RealBiz.
“We’ve also seen a significant uptick in our social media services so the decision was made to combine a social media management software into the backend of NestBuilder. We are trying to give agents a tool that can manage most facets of their business without ever needing to sign onto multiple accounts,” said Aliksanyan. 
NestBuilder’s social media management program has continued to show impressive results - more than doubling its usership month-over-month.
Other NestBuilder upgrades include:
     Craigslist auto-publish listings
    ReachFactor review integration
    Map search
    Facebook Likes campaigns
    Promoted Listings
    Mobile Apps
    Enhanced customer loyalty 
These upgrades will make NestBuilder the only portal in the industry with these abilities and in essence will turn NestBuilder into the first portal designed with agent success and consumer usage in mind.
About RealBiz Media Group, Inc.
RealBiz Media Group, Inc. is a real estate digital media and technology company whose proprietary video processing technology makes it one of the leaders in providing home video tours to the real estate industry. Its client base reaches more than 350,000 real estate agents and brokers. The company provides a series of products including a consumer portal at http://www.nestbuilder.com, an agent-only platform known as Nestbuilder Agent, an agent social media and marketing solution known as ReachFactor, a growing MVA network, virtual tours and mobile apps. The company enjoys access to many of the nation's largest real estate companies with numerous approved vendors and national contracts.
